  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Objective**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the project scope: a free iOS mobile app for business card scanning and contact saving. This aligns perfectly with the existing web app built in React/TypeScript within Google AI Studio Build. I\'m exploring the functionality from an iOS perspective to maintain scope.\n\n\n**Refining the Approach**\n\nI\'ve decided a native iOS app isn\'t feasible, so I\'m pivoting to a PWA or mobile-responsive web app optimized for Safari. This approach streamlines camera integration for scanning and OCR/AI text extraction using Gemini Pro Vision. I\'m focusing on features: camera, OCR, data saving (local or cloud), and mobile-friendly UI/UX.\n\n\n**Implementing the Core Features**\n\nI\'m now diving into the implementation plan. I\'ve decided to prioritize a server.ts backend with an Express setup to extract data from images. My goal is to create an API endpoint that can handle image uploads (base64) and interface with Gemini for structured JSON output. Local storage appears the best option for now to store the parsed data. For camera integration, I\'m leaning heavily towards the HTML5 file input, which appears the most reliable for iOS Safari.\n\n\n**Structuring the Frontend**\n\nI\'m now outlining the frontend UI. I\'m focusing on a mobile-first layout with a bottom navigation bar for scanner and contacts views. The scanner view will feature a camera button, image preview, and processing indicator. The contacts view will be a list of saved cards. There will also be a view to edit or save data extracted from images. I plan to use `localStorage` for state management via a custom `useContacts` hook. I also need to update the metadata.\n\n\n**Implementing the Backend**\n\nI\'m now focusing on integrating the Google GenAI library with the backend using Express. I intend to create a server.ts file, incorporating a suitable file upload format and integrating Google GenAI to handle image uploads and extract structured JSON output. I will also incorporate `@google/genai` library and use an API key. I will update the `package.json` file for the backend scripts and related dependencies.\n\n\n**Building the API Endpoint**\n\nI\'m currently working on building the `/api/extract` endpoint using Express, configuring it to accept base64 image data (with a 10MB limit), and integrating the Google GenAI library. I\'ve successfully cleaned the base64 string and prepared the request for the Gemini Pro Vision model, specifying JSON output with a defined schema. I\'m structuring the prompt to include details like name, job title, company, phone, email, website and address.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Parsing**\n\nI\'m now integrating the backend JSON parsing with the frontend state management and API calls. I\'m focusing on the `App.tsx` file and state definition. I need to define state variables for `view` (\'contacts\', \'scan\', \'edit\'), the `contacts` array, and the `currentScan` object to display the parsed business card data in the `edit` view. I\'m also ensuring the camera input is functional with the appropriate HTML input element.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 727472844
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
