  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering UI Design**\n\nOkay, I\'ve decided on a dark gradient with white text and transparent glass panels. I\'m starting to think about modifications, particularly within `App.tsx`. I already read through `App.tsx`. Now, I\'m focusing on that `div` with the Tailwind classes.\n\n\n**Refining the Visuals**\n\nI\'ve altered the container, prioritizing a `min-h-screen` and adjusted the text color. The header now features a backdrop blur with a shadow and the chevron\'s hover color is updated. I\'ve also implemented modifications for the empty state of the contact list, using a translucent background, white text with a slight shadow, and updated text, enhancing the visual appeal and consistency of the UI.\n\n\n**Adjusting Text Emphasis**\n\nI\'m currently working to emphasize key details and clarify text within the application. Specifically, I\'ve modified the initial prompt on the landing page, updating a direct text element to make it stand out. Additionally, I\'ve updated the styling of the text on contact cards for improved readability.\n\n\n**Improving Contact Card Appearance**\n\nI\'ve revised the contact card\'s button element to improve visual appeal. I\'ve updated its design to feature a translucent white background with a blur effect, a shadow, and a subtle border. I\'ve also incorporated a transition effect on hover, a circular initial placeholder with the contact\'s name, and updated text styling.\n\n\n**Enhancing Visual Elements**\n\nI\'m now focused on refining the visual elements using Tailwind classes. Specifically, I\'ve updated the appearance of the main `div` container to include a white background with a blur effect, shadow, and border. Furthermore, I\'ve enhanced the \"Save\" button with a translucent white background, blur, shadow, and transition effects. I\'m also planning to modify the contact detail header and placeholder images.\n\n\n**Refining Header Elements**\n\nI\'ve updated the contact detail header within the UI. I\'ve switched the circular placeholder to a white background with a blur and shadow, along with a white border. I\'ve incorporated a gradient background from white to transparent, covering the entire inset of the placeholder, creating a subtle visual effect.\n\n\n**Modifying UI Elements**\n\nI\'m now revising the contact detail display. I\'ve updated the contact\'s initial placeholder to a circular element with the first letter of their name, or a user icon if no name is available. The text now includes a drop shadow. I\'m also changing the \"Delete Contact\" button to a red background with white text, and a confirmation prompt to ensure contact deletion is intentional.\n\n\n**Implementing Delete Confirmation**\n\nI\'ve just added a confirmation prompt to the \"Delete Contact\" button using JavaScript\'s `window.confirm`. I\'m now verifying the functionality to ensure that the user can confirm or cancel the action. The delete button now employs a red visual style to signal the serious nature of the action.\n\n\n**Adding New Functionality**\n\nI\'ve just added two new buttons to the contacts view, one to scan and import and another to add contacts manually. They\'re at the bottom and are styled with Tailwind classes. The manual add button will switch the view to \"editor\". The scan button triggers the file input.\n\n\n**Refining Button Functionality**\n\nI\'ve just styled the \"Scan\" and \"Manual Add\" buttons at the bottom of the contacts view. The scan button, when clicked, triggers the file input element. The manual add button will move the view to the editor, making contact creation smoother and simpler. I\'ve updated both buttons with new classes for enhanced visual presentation and a transition effect.\n\n\n**Updating Form Elements**\n\nI\'ve just implemented a reusable `FormField` component with an icon, label, input field, and associated styling. The component includes error handling and improved visual feedback. The placeholder text dynamically updates based on the label, making the form more user-friendly. I\'ve also incorporated basic validation, and have started to integrate it into the contact editor.\n\n\n**Implementing Detail Row**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `DetailRow` component for displaying contact details, including phone, email, and URL. It conditionally renders based on the presence of a value, and provides clickable links for supported types. The content uses a white background, rounded corners, and a subtle shadow for better visual separation.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 47
      nanos: 972943530
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
