  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Adding Settings Menu**\n\nI\'m focusing on incorporating a settings menu, positioned top-left. Key features will be language selection\342\200\224English and Vietnamese, complete with UI translations. Also, theme customization with modern color palettes will be included, and I\'ll revisit the current CSS-generated liquid glass background.\n\n\n**Considering Theme Implementation**\n\nI\'m now exploring how best to apply themes. I\'m thinking of adding a class to the `body` or `html` element, using inline styles, or perhaps CSS variables. I\'m looking at `src/App.tsx` and considering the best way to integrate the settings view. Adding \"settings\" to the existing `view` state seems the easiest, rather than a modal. I\'m also preparing for translation and theme implementation with CSS variables.\n\n\n**Refining Background Implementation**\n\nI\'ve determined it\'s simpler to manage the background on the root `div` within `App.tsx` because of `min-h-screen`. This will make it fill the screen nicely. I\'m now referencing the styling currently in `index.css` to transition it. I\'m now also adding a `THEMES` constant in `App.tsx` to hold theme configurations.\n\n\n**Defining Theme and Translation**\n\nI\'ve crafted a `THEMES` constant with color configurations and gradients for different themes. I\'m also now focusing on translations, I\'m planning to define English and Vietnamese translations in a `t` object for ease of use. It will be helpful. I\'m considering using `useEffect` on `document.body` for background application.\n\n\n**Defining UI Strings**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining all the necessary UI strings, including those for the profile and contact management sections. This includes labels, prompts, and confirmation messages such as \"My Profile,\" \"Edit Profile,\" \"Save Contact,\" \"Delete Contact,\" and error messages. I\'m taking into account labels for each input on the contact form to ensure everything\'s clear.\n\n\n**Defining UI Strings (cont.)**\n\nI\'m expanding the translation object. I\'ve added Vietnamese translations for \"My Cards,\" \"Scanning,\" \"Review Details,\" \"Edit Contact,\" \"Contact,\" \"My Profile,\" \"Edit Profile,\" \"Settings,\" \"Search Placeholder,\" \"All,\" \"No Matches,\" \"No Cards,\" \"Try Adjusting,\" \"Tap to Scan,\" \"Full Name,\" \"Job Title,\" \"Company,\" \"Phone,\" \"Email,\" \"Website,\" \"Address,\" and \"Tags\". This brings the UI\'s translation coverage into better shape. I\'m focusing on user flows next.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 14
      nanos: 229989969
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
