  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Login Alternatives**\n\nI\'ve got a clearer picture now. The Firebase setup is out, but they still want login functionality for specific features. I\'m focusing on \"opt-in\" login, triggered by the user\'s need for data synchronization, backup, contact sharing, and advanced features. CRM integration and Google sync are also in the mix. I\'m evaluating options that allow this selective approach, avoiding mandatory initial login.\n\n\n**Refining Sync Implementation**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the UI/UX for cloud sync and premium features. The core is an \"opt-in\" experience in the settings menu. Clicking on \"Cloud Sync & Premium Features\" will lead to a mock setup explaining benefits, followed by a \"Login/Sign Up\" button. Since the backend\'s not there yet, it will alert \"Coming Soon\" for now. I\'m exploring an `auth` view to handle this transition.\n\n\n**Implementing Account Access**\n\nI\'m leaning towards an \"Account\" view, either replacing or working within the existing Settings. I\'m focusing on the `App.tsx` file now, to translate cloud features. Specifically, I added translations for \"Cloud Sync & Premium,\" login benefits, and various benefits like data sync, backup, contact sharing, CRM integration, AI features, and Google/Outlook sync. I also added translations for login methods: Google, Apple, and Email. The plan is to present these options in a new view when the user is not logged in.\n\n\n"
